theorem closure_interior_closure_interior_eq_closure_interior
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    closure (interior (closure (interior A))) = closure (interior A) := by
  apply subset_antisymm
  ·
    -- `interior (closure (interior A))` is contained in `closure (interior A)`
    have h₁ : interior (closure (interior A)) ⊆ closure (interior A) :=
      interior_subset
    -- Taking closures preserves the subset relation.
    have : closure (interior (closure (interior A)))
        ⊆ closure (closure (interior A)) := closure_mono h₁
    simpa [closure_closure] using this
  ·
    -- `interior A` is contained in `interior (closure (interior A))`
    have h₂ : interior A ⊆ interior (closure (interior A)) :=
      interior_mono (subset_closure : (interior A : Set X) ⊆ closure (interior A))
    -- Taking closures preserves the subset relation.
    have : closure (interior A) ⊆ closure (interior (closure (interior A))) :=
      closure_mono h₂
    simpa using this

theorem P1_of_dense_interior {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hDense : closure (interior A) = (Set.univ : Set X)) :
    Topology.P1 A := by
  dsimp [Topology.P1]
  intro x hxA
  have : x ∈ (Set.univ : Set X) := Set.mem_univ x
  simpa [hDense] using this
